{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 186334, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "93626", "body": "He is changed from lvl 59 to 56 in 2.3. Very suprised.\r\n\r\nEdit: but still very hard for lvl 56 groups", "date": "2007-11-17T12:51:44-06:00", "rating": 28, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2007-11-17T12:55:11-06:00", 1, "93626"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 207922, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "110029", "body": "A note on Princess Moira Bronzebeard: I can verify that she can't be shackled, Mind Controlled, feared or seduced. We just tanked her, though there is probably a better way using a hunter to kite or possibly netting her.\r\n\r\nJust know that she will try to heal Emperor Thaurissan, so make sure your strategy handles this point.", "date": "2007-12-27T00:24:52-06:00", "rating": 22, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Kited her successfully as a mage while the rest of the party focused fire on the Emperor. There are only two things to take note here:  1) You don't want to lose her attention, so make sure to hit her regularly so that she doesn't have time to focus on the Emperor. Instant spells work wonders here. 2) Make good use of the ramps at the sides of the room. Run up one of them, then jump down the ledge and run to the other across the room. This will give you breathing space if Moira tends to catch up with you, as she cannot jump off the ledge and will take a longer route down the ramp.  All that do", "creationdate": "2007-12-27T00:24:53-06:00", "id": 404577, "rating": 3, "commentid": 207922, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "179242", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Immune to Polymorph as of 2.4.2", "creationdate": "2008-07-02T16:42:01-05:00", "id": 340200, "rating": 2, "commentid": 207922, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "73381", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 216613, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "102489", "body": "Can this be soloed by a 70 rogue?  might be hard since I understand there are 2 characters (bosses)", "date": "2008-01-11T05:20:50-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes this can be soloed by almost any class if you use the right tactics (not my idea saw it on a video and my apologies to the original for not remembering the name). Start of by bursting down the princess; she has about as much health as the elites from the rest of the instance. Follow up by kiting Emp to the middle of each raised platform on either side. Jump down and run to the other side and he will be forced to run back down the stairs. Bandage while he is taking the long way and it should be cake.", "creationdate": "2008-01-14T12:09:37-06:00", "id": 322413, "rating": 0, "commentid": 216613, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "45880", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yes, it can be solo'ed by a 70 Rogue. I just did it, with only a few epics (Mace/Hemo Specc).  Emperor get extremely #$%^ed off as you down princess, but she heals him so I just tanked her first. She dropped really fast. Emperor starts getting mad and starts hitting for around 600+ damage, dropping your hp quick. Might need a potion.   Otherwise it's pretty easy if you know how to play a rogue.  On a side note: You can kill the Princess, and Vanish and bandage, and she will not respawn.", "creationdate": "2008-03-10T19:02:37-05:00", "id": 328391, "rating": 0, "commentid": 216613, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Masterkace", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This can be soloed by any 70 without any tacts at all, if you just know how to play. But let me tell you, it is NOT possible to kill the boss without killing the adds first ^^ found it out the hard way", "creationdate": "2008-04-02T03:49:22-05:00", "id": 29907, "rating": 17, "commentid": 216613, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Alzira", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can kill easy without clearing, I'll do it on my tanking warrior when bored for http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11684, just tank and spank with a shield wall and last stand in there, should have more then enough time to loot before dieing.", "creationdate": "2008-04-15T00:25:16-05:00", "id": 332212, "rating": 1, "commentid": 216613, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "106924", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "you can do this with a protpaladin pulling the whole room , but you need to have the trinket that drops from shattered halls (heals when an atk is blocked , use effekt)", "creationdate": "2008-06-25T00:56:25-05:00", "id": 339304, "rating": 4, "commentid": 216613, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Chinabux", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 288747, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sandos", "body": "He's immune to arcane damage.", "date": "2008-05-15T14:27:07-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He should only be immune to arcane (and all magic damage) when he uses his 'Avatar of Flame' ability; he grows in size and appears to burn, which lasts 10 seconds.", "creationdate": "2008-07-02T22:18:20-05:00", "id": 38239, "rating": 15, "commentid": 288747, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Auben", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 300856, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "159803", "body": "If you have the princess quest (so you have to keep her alive), you don't generally have to worry much. I've downed the emperor several times... as long as you have a good tank/healer, you can leave the princess to hit on the tank and it's not a big deal. \r\n\r\nMAKE SURE YOU DON'T USE AOE IF YOU NEED TO SAVE THE PRINCESS!\r\n\r\nAlso, be sure to clear EVERYTHING in the room before the emperor. Easy enough, mage AoE is helpful here... and if you pull correctly, you can get the elites seperate from the other mobs.", "date": "2008-06-06T20:51:43-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can hurt her all you like (e.g. kick, earthshock, shield bash to interrupt her heals, any aoe), as long as the Emperor dies first you should be fine.", "creationdate": "2008-07-02T22:20:58-05:00", "id": 38240, "rating": 6, "commentid": 300856, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Auben", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
