{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 632254, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "332795", "body": "As an 80 hunter I was able to kill the boss without killing anything else in the room and then aoe down the adds with no problems, I had about 6k health left when I was done. So if you're doing this and you're confident in your aoe, hit the boss hard so he dies, you get the achievement and then see what you can get your dps up to by aoe'ing the rest of the room. It's pretty fun, pointless, but fun.", "date": "2009-03-05T13:37:05-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Solo'd this as a 60 Ret paladin, fairly twinked 6081hp.  Used the Lava swim to get to him, Lyceum is pretty easy to solo, as is Magmar. The mobs in his hall can be tough if they run and pull another group, but u have enough cd's to survive it(make sure u remove amplify damage when they apply it aswell).  The most difficult bit of the fight is when their both up at the same time, but the princess isnt immune to stuns so stun+unload on her to get her out of the way asap.  The real killer is the Hand of Thaurissan stun he does, can cause u to take a dangerous amount of dmg so save bubble/LoH/trin", "creationdate": "2009-03-05T13:37:06-06:00", "id": 395972, "rating": 1, "commentid": 632254, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "48416", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 695007, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "258919", "body": "I even had troubles with this as an 80 frost mage, because I was trying not to kill the Princess for the quest. For casters, it all depends on whether or not he uses the anti-magic shield. So I dualspecced to arcane and popped Arcane Power and Icy Veins. I won, because he never had time to put up the shield.\r\n\r\n\r\nSo for casters trying to solo it, the key is to kill him before he can pop up his shield.\r\n\r\n\r\nAnyways, if you want a way to get to him fast (just to get the achievement kill or for a quest)\r\n\r\n[b]Shortcut to the Emperor[/b]\r\n\r\nFor this method you WILL need the Shadowforge Key. In addition, a high amount of fire absorption, a health potion, bandages, and maybe a shield/damage reduction spell would help, depending on your level. As a mage, I just used ice bubble/fire ward. \r\n\r\n\r\n1) Enter the instance and take a left. Unlock the door.\r\n2) Walk down the hall and unlock the door at the end. You'll be in a long hallway\r\n3) Go right and pass through the gate. Continue along until you reach Lord Incendius. Kill him or not, then put on your shields and fire protection and jump off the west side of the platform that Incendius is on into the lava.\r\n4) Head north and a bit east, stopping wherever there's a platform to heal the lava damage. Watch out, because there are fire elementals in the lava that will attack you.\r\n5) Head to the Molten Core bridge and look for a ramp on the western end of it. Climb up, go to the hallway to the west, and take a right.\r\n\r\nNow, you've skipped almost all of Blackrock Depths. All that's left is the torch room and Magmus, then you're at the boss room.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=1584:]Here[/url] is a map of this route.", "date": "2009-04-26T14:03:45-05:00", "rating": 74, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You first need the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11000]Shadowforge Key[/url] to access the room where the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=9956]Shadowforge Flame Keepers[/url] are located.  This [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=1584:558077559130589106528108537085538133579128579075]Map[/url] shows where the  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=9956]Shadowforge Flame Keepers[/url] are located, they will drop the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11885]Shadowforge Torches[/url] which are needed to light the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11885]Brazers (map)[/url]in the same room. This will o", "creationdate": "2009-04-26T14:03:46-05:00", "id": 410697, "rating": 11, "commentid": 695007, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "desiday", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[b]Thank you[/b], useful and exactly what I was looking for :)   [u]Little addendum[/u]  To [b][u]open the doors right before the final boss[/u][/b] you need 2x [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11885]Shadowforge Torch[/url] obtained just killing 2x [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=9956]Shadowforge Flame Keeper[/url]. Kil lthem, get the torches and light the braziers. The doors will immediately open.", "creationdate": "2009-05-08T05:20:33-05:00", "id": 96670, "rating": 20, "commentid": 695007, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LoqueNahak", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This was SO helpful in navigating around BRD. No matter how many times I do this instance, there is always long enough of a gap to forget how to do it. >< Thanks for being so detailed! It really really helped!", "creationdate": "2009-07-30T23:23:46-05:00", "id": 417960, "rating": 2, "commentid": 695007, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "367098", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ahh, the famous shortcut, amazing that I was using it on patch 1.12 (like two years ago) and here we are, at patch 3.1.1, and someone finally mentions it :D", "creationdate": "2009-08-09T11:09:53-05:00", "id": 419490, "rating": 5, "commentid": 695007, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "386867", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I very much appreciate the preceding posts:   1) I used the map and the shortcut to get to the Lyceum.  2) Then I found the Shadowflame Keepers to get the torches.  3) Then I lit the braziers -- and the big doors OPENED!  4) Once in the room, I took a bit of extra time and killed all the adds first. I was glad I did, because the emperor and his girlfriend were something of a handful.", "creationdate": "2010-12-29T22:16:13-06:00", "id": 209710, "rating": 2, "commentid": 695007, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "fordahord", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-26T14:45:51-05:00", 3, "258919"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 867833, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "error10", "body": "Ridiculously easy solo as a 74 shadow priest. Probably could have done it at 70 or even earlier.\n\nPop Shadowfiend on the princess; this will prevent her from getting heals off. PW:S and dot up and Mind Flay the emperor until he's dead. Should take 30 seconds or less. Turn in your quest and enjoy.\n\nOh, and there's no way to skip Magmus.\n\nOther hints: Spam Holy Nova in the Lyceum if you pull the mobs there. They go down very fast. They also respawn very fast. Watch your mana while you're in this room.", "date": "2009-10-16T08:22:36-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-10-16T08:30:36-05:00", 1, "error10"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 912424, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "StevieWonder", "body": "Flames spurt out from the walls. This can give your group a fair bit of trouble", "date": "2009-12-10T12:51:05-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 955464, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gubugu", "body": "Each Dwarf Clan have their Leader their Capital city and their Affiliation\n\nAffiliation:\n\nBronzebeard, Wildhammers and Frostborn Dwarfes = Alliance\nDark Iron = Before -  Ragnaros, Now -  Alliance\nIron = Loken\n\n\nLeaders:\n\nBronzebeard = Representative Muradin\nWildhammer = Representative Falstad\nFrostborn = King Yorg Stormheart\nDark Iron = Representative Moira\nIron = Loken\n\n\n\nCapital City\n\n\nBronzebeard = Ironforge (Dun Morogh)\nWildhammer = Some in Aerie Peak (The Hinterlands) and Some in Ironforge\nFrostborn = Frosthold (Storm Peaks)\nDark Iron = Before -  Shadowforge City (Blackrock Mountain - Searing Gorge) - Now - Ironforge\nIron = Thor Modan (Grizzly Hills)", "date": "2010-01-24T09:50:59-06:00", "rating": 28, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-01-11T10:27:21-06:00", 2, "gubugu"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 958233, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "311227", "body": "He was the first hard mode fight in WoW^^\r\nKill the princess first=normal mode\r\nKill him first and get the quest for her=hard mode", "date": "2010-01-27T15:25:01-06:00", "rating": 38, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Don't forget super hard mode -- Pull him without full clearing the room :P  Edit in response to Karasuramen below:  Almost any class at 80 could solo the whole room at one pull. Some would require planning (Rogues still may not be able to do it), others wouldn't.  Even at 54, I easily tanked this boss with the princess up, it's honestly not that much harder, but I would not have thought to pull the boss with more than one pull left up.  Edit: It seems at some point in one of the last few patches, he no longer pulls the remaining mobs.", "creationdate": "2010-02-25T19:22:55-06:00", "id": 151241, "rating": 4, "commentid": 958233, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Pwntiff", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Back then i'm sure.  Super easy now as a ret pally in half relentless, half wrathful pvp gear :).  I was feeling lazy so I just nitro boosted past the guards, judged him to pull, ran up behind the throne, and just spammed consecrate to kill all the adds and lazily auto-attacked him to death.  Good times :)  Also by sheer random chance he dropped ironfoe... and I was just killing him on a whim for the achievement after getting my repair bot schematic for jeeves O.o.", "creationdate": "2010-02-28T05:50:37-06:00", "id": 443540, "rating": 0, "commentid": 958233, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "549667", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "We just did this.  2 frost mages Hunter Priest healer-me Druid tank  the two mages did their Nova> Blizzard, I spammed Holy Nova and Hunter volley. The druid tanked the Boss while Hunters pet tanked Princces.  I dunno what the mages did but the mobs never reached them, man that was fun.", "creationdate": "2010-03-13T22:02:29-06:00", "id": 444720, "rating": 0, "commentid": 958233, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "217067", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ya frost mage's blizzard if permanently channeled can hold a target in place for like ever. With two the mobs probably instantly froze in place and got chain frozen", "creationdate": "2010-05-31T16:08:53-05:00", "id": 451097, "rating": 0, "commentid": 958233, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "405835", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 1095609, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "637791", "body": "I just love Emperor Dagran Thaurissan, and when i changed my dwarf to rp server 2 week ago, i wanted to make rp set for him, and this is what i came up with:\r\nhttp://www.wowhead.com/compare?items=11924:11684:44107:20969:20159:51970.-88", "date": "2010-08-04T14:29:49-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 1103281, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "jhneoh", "body": "Just did this 2 man, 57 Pally and Priest\r\n\r\nBrought him down to 50% hp fairly easily, but at that point the Princess started spamming heals on him. Only managed to kill him when she went oom.\r\n\r\nOtherwise a fairly simple fight.", "date": "2010-08-18T21:27:15-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 1103420, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lyom", "body": "If, using the Random Dungeon tool, you were queued for Upper City, just killed him, and got no Random Dungeon completion message, then you likely killed [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=9018]High Interrogator Gerstahn[/url] before him.\r\nThis makes the random dungeon tool bug out and not reward any sachet at all.\r\n\r\nMost of the times, you can tell whether you are queued for Prison or Upper City by looking at the level range of your group. Once Prison is green to you and Upper City yellow, you are likely queued for Upper City.", "date": "2010-08-19T03:16:08-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 1195831, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "415054", "body": "In 4.0.3a his aggro quote changed from \"Come to the aid of the Throne!\" to \"I will crush you into little tiny pieces!\". In addition he won't aggro the remaining adds anymore.", "date": "2010-11-29T13:52:19-06:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "And after 5.1 Moira has been replaced by a Dark iron high priestess.", "creationdate": "2020-09-28T13:00:30-05:00", "id": 1392847, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1195831, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KenjiT28", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 1285281, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ilsor", "body": "The most badass character in the game. He rules a friggin empire of fire, he is a dwarf and he has a booming name. He has a lot of experienced lieutenants who command thousands of skilled soldiers, engineers and golems. His capital isn't ruined (heck, it isn't even slightly damaged), his squads patrol the place, he has dozens of captured people in his prison, he has a bar with ETC, mindf**king mechanism for gaining access to his chamber and unique Dark Iron anvil and forge. He isn't sieged by Blackrock orcs from nearby BRS. I hardly notice his slavery to Ragnaros.\r\n\r\nAnd ye, he also has a lady. Under his full control.\r\n\r\nIf he wasn't killable, I'd say he's the most successful NPC in the game.", "date": "2011-01-09T05:15:03-06:00", "rating": 48, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Really? Do the words \"Prepare to meet your doom at the hands of Ragnaros' most powerful servant\" mean anything to you? I mean, he's not exactly subtle about it. Other than that, and the fact that he's considered long dead, yeah you're right.", "creationdate": "2014-04-19T21:22:02-05:00", "id": 741444, "rating": -2, "commentid": 1285281, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LanceofAbel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You said his kingdom isn't even slightly ruined. -_- Really? Are you blind? All of Blackrock mountain was his domain. Blackrock spire (upper/lower) were taken by the orcs in the first war. Blackwing lair is another place where the Dark Irons once inhabited. They were forced down into one \"tiny\" section of the mountain.", "creationdate": "2020-09-28T10:20:43-05:00", "id": 1392814, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1285281, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KenjiT28", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-01-09T15:20:24-06:00", 6, "Ilsor"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 1287889, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "705938", "body": "i thought this place never ended lol", "date": "2011-01-10T17:24:26-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Even in BFA there's a huge number of encounters in this place including some \"hidden\" ones. Soloing at 120 takes a long time only because of how big the place is, and the need to loot everything to get the coffer keys.", "creationdate": "2020-09-28T12:56:03-05:00", "id": 1392845, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1287889, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KenjiT28", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 1310045, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Muzzle248", "body": "You can sit in his throne :)", "date": "2011-01-26T00:17:37-06:00", "rating": 22, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Kinda feels wrong to do so after having downed him on a Dark Iron dwarf. But no king rules forever. ;-)", "creationdate": "2020-09-28T12:58:47-05:00", "id": 1392846, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1310045, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KenjiT28", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 1333512, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Thanetor", "body": "This sucks. Alot.\r\n\r\nSo, I was farming Ironfoe for a long time on my warrior for RP purposes (Yes, I'm on an RP server.)\r\nAfter about 50 times, I finally gave up. About a year later, I was on my friend's account running it to get him the achievement...\r\n\r\n\r\n[i]That bastard DROPPED.[/i]", "date": "2011-02-12T16:22:50-06:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 1333514, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Thanetor", "body": "Farming the Circle of Flame. This was another drop that dropped once when I didn't need it, but doesn't drop when I did.", "date": "2011-02-12T16:23:52-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 1428271, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "CircleofHealing", "body": "He says something along the lines of \"I'm going to cut (tear) you into little pieces\" not sure if this is a Pink Floyd reference to their song [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_of_These_Days_%28Pink_Floyd_song%29]\"One of these days\"[/url], where the only lyric is \"One of these days I'm going to cut you into little pieces.\"", "date": "2011-05-26T18:50:50-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 1440114, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheRealLink", "body": "Thanks for posting about the doors... There are SO MANY dwarves in the Lyceum that I'd have probably been lost for awhile.  You can kill the groups easily as they all have ~730 health each but once I was barely even a portion done near one of the halls, the groups respawned.  None are lootable except for the more elite mobs / fire elementals in the room it seems like.\r\n\r\nOnly the Torchbearers drop torches - they were for me, hiding closely to columns and not at the center or with any groups.  Once you get two torches, light each torch left and right of the doors and they'll open.\r\n\r\nNow for the Emperor's room, I happened to clear out the room first (got the Senator removal line so knew that was safe) before I fought the couple.  Killed Princess first then the Emperor - he didn't seem to do anything particularly nasty to me at 67 - just has a lot of HP (near 70,000).  Barely lived by using my regular CDs and recovery pots but very doable.  I presume as others said, a lv 70 would make easy work of him.  \r\n\r\nNow that's some feeling of accomplishment!  To finally kill the Emperor and see the achievement for BRD!", "date": "2011-06-12T16:24:37-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 1662263, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lifeslowlydies", "body": "Emperor Dagran Thaurissan yells:\n\n[quote]Is that the best you can do? Do you really expect you could defeat someone as awe inspiring as me?[/quote]\n\n[quote]Ha! You can't even begin to imagine the futility of your efforts.[/quote]\n\n[quote]I will crush you into little tiny pieces![/quote]", "date": "2012-05-03T16:10:48-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-05-03T16:37:09-05:00", 1, "lifeslowlydies"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 1725714, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kjorval", "body": "After a quite successfull solo-run with my monk (lvl 55) i failed to kill the emperor. he delivers an enormous punch. I was too shocked to check my Battlelog, but it was about 3k (20% leather migation). I had no chance to bring guard up, or even shuffle. \r\n\r\nBesides that, he has his 5 sek stun. Without guard active and nearly full hp, he can take you down. A intersting difficult fight. Maybe i come back later for him, with BC Gear. \r\n\r\n\r\nAnd yes, for a dwarf, he is indeed a pretty impressing charackter. And shadowforge city... damn, one hell of a city it is.", "date": "2012-09-30T07:24:53-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Any player with a chain stun would be depicted as a coward and an unfair advantage. I have yet to find out what makes unfair advantages OK for an NPC. His stun literally has no cooldown and will be cast again as soon as it's about to wear off. When you're lucky, you can use an ability but don't count on it. It has a relatively high range so don't even try to outrun it. Still, kiting them around until his sidekick is down, if you can manage that, you should be alright fighting Dagran on his own. His damage can be countered by a tanky class with heal, it's his stun that's the real danger.", "creationdate": "2014-05-01T22:04:50-05:00", "id": 743668, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1725714, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Guanyin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
